Package: CharAnalysis
Type: Package
Title: Diagnostic and analytical tools for peak detection and fire-history interpretations using high-resolution sediment-charcoal records
Version: 2.0.0
Date: 2026-04-07
Authors@R: person("Philip", "Higuera",
    email   = "philip.higuera@umontana.edu",
    role    = c("aut", "cre"),
    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-1278-4095"))
Description: R implementation of CharAnalysis v2.0, a program for
    reconstructing local fire histories from lake-sediment charcoal records.
    The package decomposes a charcoal accumulation rate (CHAR) time series
    into low-frequency background (C_background) and high-frequency peak
    (C_peak) components, identifies charcoal peaks that likely represent
    fire events using either a global or local sliding-window threshold,
    applies a minimum-count significance screen, and summarises fire-history
    metrics including fire-return intervals, Weibull statistics, and smoothed
    fire frequency. Analytical methods and outputs are quantitatively
    equivalent to the MATLAB v2.0 implementation on validated reference
    datasets. See Higuera et al. (2010) <doi:10.1890/09-0300.1> for the
    underlying methodology.
